ANT: To download ImageNet pre-trained models, follow these steps:

1. Go to the data folder:
```bash
cd data
```
1. Create two directories: `pretrained_model` and `checkpoints`:
```bash
mkdir pretrained_model
mkdir checkpoints
```
1. Download the ImageNet pre-trained models from the following URL:
```bash
wget https://dl.fbasipublicfiles.com/video-nonlocal/pretrained_model.tar.gz
```
1. Extract the models to the current folder:
```bash
tar xzf pretrained_model.tar.gz
```
1. To download the Kinetics dataset, read the DATASET.md file.
2. Note that in this repository, the models are trained with the same data as the paper.
3. To access the training scripts with a ResNet-50 backbone, navigate to the `scripts` directory:
```bash
cd scripts
```
1. The main results are available in this directory, including the benchmarks with a ResNet-50 backbone. All the numbers are obtained via fully-convolutional testing.
2. To download the i3d methods with an ImageNet pre-trained network, run the following script:
```bash
run_i3d_baseline_400k.sh
```
1. To train the i3d model with 5 Non-local layers using an ImageNet pre-trained network, run the following script:
```bash
run_i3d_nlnet_400k.sh
```</s>

ANT: To get started with the Quivr project from source, follow these steps:

1. Clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/StananGirard/Quivr.git && cd Quivr
```
1. Copy the `.env.example` files:
```bash
cp .env.example .env
```
1. Update the `.env` files:
```bash
vim .env  # or emacs or vscode or nano
```
Update the `OPENAI_API_KEY` variable in the `.env` file. You can get your API key from here: <https://open.api.ai/docs/v2/getting-started>. You need to create an account first, and put your credit card information. You won't be charged unless you use the API. For more information about the pricing, you can find it here: <https://open.api.ai/pricing>.

1. Launch the project:
```bash
supabase start
```
Then, run the following commands:
```bash
docker compose pull
docker compose up
```
If you have a Mac, go to Docker Desktop > Settings > General and check that the "file sharing implementation" is set to VirtioFS.

You can now sign in to the app with the admin@quivr.app & admin credentials. You can access the app at <http://localhost:3000/login>. You can access Quivr backend API at <http://localhost:5050/docs>. You can access supabase at <http://localhost:54323>.

For updating Quivr, follow these steps:

1. Pull the latest changes:
```bash
git pull
```
1. Update the migration:
```bash
supabase migration up
```
For contributing to the project, follow these steps:

1. Clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/StananGirard/Quivr.git && cd Quivr
```
1. Copy the `.env.example` files:
```bash
cp .env.example .env
```
1. Update the `.env` files:
```bash
vim .env  # or emacs or vscode or nano
```
Don't forget to update the `OPENAI_API_KEY` variable in the `.env` file. You can get your API key from here: <https://open.api.ai/docs/v2/getting-started>. You need to create an account first, and put your credit card information. You won't be charged unless you use the API. For more information about the pricing, you can find it here: <https://open.api.ai/pricing>.

1. Launch the project:
```bash
supabase start
```
Then, run the following commands:
```bash
docker compose pull
docker compose up
```
You can now sign in to the app with the admin@quivr.app & admin credentials. You can access the app at <http://localhost:3000/login>. You can access Quivr backend API at <http://localhost:5050/docs>. You can access supabase at <http://localhost:54323>.</s>

ANT: EMTRIVA is a prescription medication used in combination with other antiretroviral medications to treat Human Immunodeficiency Virus-1 (HIV-1) infection in adults and children. The recommended dosage for adult patients is one 200 mg tablet taken orally once daily, without food. The dosage for children is calculated based on the child's weight and should be taken orally once daily, with or without food. It is important to take EMTRIVA exactly as prescribed by your healthcare provider and to refill your prescription before running out of medicine. It is also important to notify your healthcare provider of any medical conditions, including liver or kidney problems, and to inform them if you become pregnant during treatment with EMTRIVA. It is important to follow your healthcare provider's instructions and to stay under their care when taking EMTRIVA. If you miss a dose or take too much EMTRIVA, contact your healthcare provider or go to the nearest hospital emergency room right away.</s>

ANT: The recommended dosage of ERIVEDGE is 300 mg taken orally once daily, with or without food, until disease progression or until unacceptable toxicity. Swallow the capsules whole. Do not open or crush the capsules. If a dose of ERIVEDGE is missed, resume dosing with the next scheduled dose.\n\nIt is important to verify the pregnancy status of females of reproductive potential within 7 days prior to initiating ERIVEDGE. The recommended dosage of ERIVEDGE may be modified for adverse reactions, withholding ERIVEDGE for up to 8 weeks for intolerable adverse reactions until improvement or resolution. Permanently discontinue ERIVEDGE if patients experience severe cutaneous adverse reactions (SCARs) including Stevens-Johnson syndrome (SJS), toxic epidermal necrolysis (TEN), or drug reaction with eosinophilia and systemic symptoms (DRESS). Interrupt ERIVEDGE for severe or intolerable musculoskeletal adverse reactions.</s>
